#   BLAME tickets: blame performance + output

`be blame` perf on inflate-bound history walks, plus output correctness/UX. Each entry below is one open ticket with its live state; a landed ticket (verify with `be log | grep BLAME-NNN`) drops off. [BLAME-002] (index-served tree descent) landed `1a5acce8`; the rest below remain. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [BLAME-001] — blame re-inflates unchanged blobs across all ancestors; compare OIDs top-down, inflate only on change.
 -  [BLAME-003] — parallelize blame's residual blob inflates across cores; needs a ruling (ROI fell after BLAME-002).
 -  [BLAME-005] — blame PRODUCES per-commit-run hunks (`{ts,verb,uri=commit:?<sha>}` + source + syntax toks) instead of a per-line gutter; the shared bro renderer (separate, needs improvement) then highlights/wraps. Removes the gutter-on-code-line breakage; subsumes [BLAME-004]'s stopgap.
BLAME-006a (blame skipped a DELETED file instead of folding an empty layer → readd
inherited the ROOT seq) landed `fa09701f`. BLAME-006b (`commit:?<root>` token-diffed
the whole initial tree — root cause a 9.5 MB binary; skip token-diff of binary blobs +
one-sided short-circuit) landed `8d66369c`. Both split from the [[BLAME-006]] umbrella scan.

